The paper discusses the ranked retrieval model and query processing in client-server databases, which are topics related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a novel approach to address the issue of diverse user preferences in tuple ranking, which involves techniques such as on-the-fly indexing, domination detection, and virtual tuple pruning, which are related to data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
